<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-11-15T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-11-15T12:00:00-05:00" n="264" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 Steering Committee/146:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the American Delegate (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1" type="to">Wilson</persName>)</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-15T12:00:00-05:00">November
                                    15, 1932—noon</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>245. Your 452, November 14, 6 p.m. Your understanding that you should
                            oppose suggestions (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>), (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) and (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>) is correct.</p>
                        <p>You should support the proposal that any system of publicity of
                            manufacture should apply also to material in stock, private and
                            state.</p>
                        <p>The convention of 1925 is still before the Senate. Therefore what we
                            contemplated was not resubmission of that treaty but an effort to secure
                            favorable action upon it by the Senate. Such effort, if made, should be
                            made as soon as possible after Congress reconvenes. For our guidance in
                            this matter, please keep us fully informed of all developments as they
                            occur.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>